headline: Lilly to launch Mounjaro pen in India to compete with Novo's weight-loss drug Wegovy
summary: HYDERABAD (Reuters) -Eli Lilly said on Thursday that India's drug regulator had approved the launch of pre-filled injector pens of its blockbuster weight-loss drug, Mounjaro, giving it more options to compete with Novo Nordisk's recently launched Wegovy.  Lilly started selling Mounjaro in India in late March for diabetes and obesity, and it was so far available only in 2.5 mg and 5 mg vials.  "With this approval, all six dosage options for Mounjaro will soon be available in India, supporting a more personalized approach to treatment," Lilly India President Winselow Tucker said.
